    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Explore AI-Related Skills\n",
        "\n",
        "Before classifying job postings as AI-related or non-AI, I first explore the skill names available in the Lightcast skills table. Since the exact Lightcast skill names are unknown, I review the most common skills and then search broadly for possible AI-related skill terms.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Top Skills in the Dataset"
      ],
      "id": "07a68e0f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "top_skills = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    skill_name,\n",
        "    skill_type,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT job_id) AS job_count\n",
        "FROM job_skill_matches\n",
        "GROUP BY\n",
        "    skill_name,\n",
        "    skill_type\n",
        "ORDER BY\n",
        "    job_count DESC\n",
        "LIMIT 100\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "top_skills_pd = top_skills.toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "style_table(top_skills_pd, {\n",
        "    \"job_count\": \"{:,.0f}\"\n",
        "})"
      ],
      "id": "977dba87",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Possible AI-Related Skills"
      ],
      "id": "798ac562"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "possible_ai_skills = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    skill_name,\n",
        "    skill_type,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT job_id) AS job_count\n",
        "FROM job_skill_matches\n",
        "WHERE\n",
        "    LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%machine%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%artificial%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%deep%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%neural%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%natural language%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%nlp%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%vision%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%generative%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%language model%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%llm%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%predictive%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%model%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%algorithm%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(skill_name) LIKE '%data science%'\n",
        "GROUP BY\n",
        "    skill_name,\n",
        "    skill_type\n",
        "ORDER BY\n",
        "    job_count DESC\n",
        "LIMIT 100\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "possible_ai_skills_pd = possible_ai_skills.toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "style_table(possible_ai_skills_pd, {\n",
        "    \"job_count\": \"{:,.0f}\"\n",
        "})"
      ],
      "id": "ee3b6acd",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "The table above is used as an exploratory step. It searches broadly for AI-related terms in Lightcast skill names. After reviewing these results, I use the confirmed AI-related skills to classify job postings into AI-related and non-AI groups.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Analysis 1: Salary Differences Between AI and Non-AI Careers\n",
        "\n",
        "This analysis classifies job postings as AI-related if they include AI or machine learning signals from either Lightcast skill tags, job titles, or job descriptions. Jobs without these AI-related signals are classified as non-AI. This combined method helps reduce missed AI-related postings that may not have AI skills tagged directly."
      ],
      "id": "ffccc6ac"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "ai_job_ids = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT DISTINCT\n",
        "    j.id AS job_id\n",
        "FROM job_postings j\n",
        "LEFT JOIN job_skill_matches s\n",
        "    ON j.id = s.job_id\n",
        "WHERE\n",
        "    LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%machine learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%artificial intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%generative artificial intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%mlops%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%natural language processing%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%deep learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%pytorch%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%artificial neural networks%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%machine learning model training%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%large language modeling%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%random forest algorithm%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(s.skill_name) LIKE '%decision tree learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.title_clean) LIKE '%machine learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.title_clean) LIKE '%artificial intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.title_clean) LIKE '%ai engineer%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.title_clean) LIKE '%ml engineer%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.title_clean) LIKE '%generative ai%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.title_clean) LIKE '%llm%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.body) LIKE '%machine learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.body) LIKE '%artificial intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.body) LIKE '%generative ai%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.body) LIKE '%large language model%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.body) LIKE '%llm%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.body) LIKE '%deep learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(j.body) LIKE '%natural language processing%'\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "ai_job_ids.createOrReplaceTempView(\"ai_job_ids\")"
      ],
      "id": "b700432f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "ai_vs_non_ai_salary = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    CASE\n",
        "        WHEN a.job_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'AI-related'\n",
        "        ELSE 'Non-AI'\n",
        "    END AS career_type,\n",
        "    ROUND(AVG(CAST(j.salary AS DOUBLE)), 2) AS avg_salary,\n",
        "    PERCENTILE_APPROX(CAST(j.salary AS DOUBLE), 0.5) AS median_salary,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT j.id) AS job_count,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT j.title_clean) AS unique_job_titles\n",
        "FROM job_postings j\n",
        "LEFT JOIN ai_job_ids a\n",
        "    ON j.id = a.job_id\n",
        "WHERE\n",
        "    j.salary IS NOT NULL\n",
        "    AND CAST(j.salary AS DOUBLE) > 0\n",
        "GROUP BY\n",
        "    CASE\n",
        "        WHEN a.job_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'AI-related'\n",
        "        ELSE 'Non-AI'\n",
        "    END\n",
        "ORDER BY\n",
        "    avg_salary DESC\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "ai_vs_non_ai_salary_pd = ai_vs_non_ai_salary.toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "ai_vs_non_ai_salary_pd[\"job_share\"] = (\n",
        "    ai_vs_non_ai_salary_pd[\"job_count\"] / ai_vs_non_ai_salary_pd[\"job_count\"].sum()\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "style_table(ai_vs_non_ai_salary_pd, {\n",
        "    \"avg_salary\": \"${:,.2f}\",\n",
        "    \"median_salary\": \"${:,.2f}\",\n",
        "    \"job_count\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"unique_job_titles\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"job_share\": \"{:.1%}\"\n",
        "})"
      ],
      "id": "f4da1eee",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "AI-related postings are identified using both Lightcast skill tags and AI-related keywords in job titles and descriptions. This combined classification reduces the chance of missing AI-related jobs that are not tagged with AI skills directly. The comparison uses only postings with valid salary values.\n",
        "\n",
        "## How do salaries differ across AI vs. non-AI careers?"
      ],
      "id": "9496af57"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "salary_distribution = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    CASE\n",
        "        WHEN a.job_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'AI-related'\n",
        "        ELSE 'Non-AI'\n",
        "    END AS career_type,\n",
        "    CAST(j.salary AS DOUBLE) AS salary\n",
        "FROM job_postings j\n",
        "LEFT JOIN ai_job_ids a\n",
        "    ON j.id = a.job_id\n",
        "WHERE\n",
        "    j.salary IS NOT NULL\n",
        "    AND CAST(j.salary AS DOUBLE) > 0\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "salary_distribution_pd = salary_distribution.toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "import plotly.express as px\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_ai_salary = px.box(\n",
        "    salary_distribution_pd,\n",
        "    x=\"career_type\",\n",
        "    y=\"salary\",\n",
        "    color=\"career_type\",\n",
        "    points=False,\n",
        "    title=\"Salary Distribution: AI vs Non-AI Careers\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_ai_salary.update_layout(\n",
        "    template=\"plotly_white\",\n",
        "    showlegend=False,\n",
        "    yaxis_title=\"Salary ($)\",\n",
        "    xaxis_title=\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_ai_salary.show()"
      ],
      "id": "51de7c3c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "AI-related roles command higher salaries than non-AI roles, with Q1, median and Q3 quartile appearing elevated.\n",
        "\n",
        "## What regions offer the highest-paying jobs in AI-related and traditional careers?"
      ],
      "id": "aac77218"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "jobs_with_ai = (\n",
        "    job_postings_df.alias(\"j\")\n",
        "    .join(\n",
        "        ai_job_ids.alias(\"a\"),\n",
        "        col(\"j.id\") == col(\"a.job_id\"),\n",
        "        \"left\"\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    .withColumn(\n",
        "        \"career_type\",\n",
        "        when(col(\"a.job_id\").isNotNull(), \"AI-related\")\n",
        "        .otherwise(\"Non-AI\")\n",
        "    )\n",
        ")\n",
        "jobs_with_ai.createOrReplaceTempView(\"jobs_with_ai\")\n",
        "\n",
        "state_salary = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    l.state_name,\n",
        "    j.career_type,\n",
        "    AVG(CAST(j.salary AS DOUBLE)) AS avg_salary\n",
        "FROM jobs_with_ai j\n",
        "JOIN locations l\n",
        "    ON j.location_id = l.location_id\n",
        "WHERE\n",
        "    j.salary IS NOT NULL\n",
        "    AND CAST(j.salary AS DOUBLE) > 0\n",
        "GROUP BY\n",
        "    l.state_name,\n",
        "    j.career_type\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "state_salary_pd = state_salary.toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "pivot_df = (\n",
        "    state_salary_pd\n",
        "    .pivot(\n",
        "        index=\"state_name\",\n",
        "        columns=\"career_type\",\n",
        "        values=\"avg_salary\"\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    .reset_index()\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "pivot_df[\"premium_dollars\"] = (\n",
        "    pivot_df[\"AI-related\"] -\n",
        "    pivot_df[\"Non-AI\"]\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "pivot_df[\"premium_pct\"] = (\n",
        "    (pivot_df[\"AI-related\"] -\n",
        "     pivot_df[\"Non-AI\"])\n",
        "    / pivot_df[\"Non-AI\"]\n",
        ") * 100\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add state abbreviation column for Plotly choropleth map\n",
        "state_abbrev = {\n",
        "    \"Alabama\": \"AL\", \"Alaska\": \"AK\", \"Arizona\": \"AZ\", \"Arkansas\": \"AR\",\n",
        "    \"California\": \"CA\", \"Colorado\": \"CO\", \"Connecticut\": \"CT\", \"Delaware\": \"DE\",\n",
        "    \"Florida\": \"FL\", \"Georgia\": \"GA\", \"Hawaii\": \"HI\", \"Idaho\": \"ID\",\n",
        "    \"Illinois\": \"IL\", \"Indiana\": \"IN\", \"Iowa\": \"IA\", \"Kansas\": \"KS\",\n",
        "    \"Kentucky\": \"KY\", \"Louisiana\": \"LA\", \"Maine\": \"ME\", \"Maryland\": \"MD\",\n",
        "    \"Massachusetts\": \"MA\", \"Michigan\": \"MI\", \"Minnesota\": \"MN\", \"Mississippi\": \"MS\",\n",
        "    \"Missouri\": \"MO\", \"Montana\": \"MT\", \"Nebraska\": \"NE\", \"Nevada\": \"NV\",\n",
        "    \"New Hampshire\": \"NH\", \"New Jersey\": \"NJ\", \"New Mexico\": \"NM\", \"New York\": \"NY\",\n",
        "    \"North Carolina\": \"NC\", \"North Dakota\": \"ND\", \"Ohio\": \"OH\", \"Oklahoma\": \"OK\",\n",
        "    \"Oregon\": \"OR\", \"Pennsylvania\": \"PA\", \"Rhode Island\": \"RI\",\n",
        "    \"South Carolina\": \"SC\", \"South Dakota\": \"SD\", \"Tennessee\": \"TN\", \"Texas\": \"TX\",\n",
        "    \"Utah\": \"UT\", \"Vermont\": \"VT\", \"Virginia\": \"VA\", \"Washington\": \"WA\",\n",
        "    \"West Virginia\": \"WV\", \"Wisconsin\": \"WI\", \"Wyoming\": \"WY\",\n",
        "    \"District of Columbia\": \"DC\"\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "pivot_df[\"state_code\"] = pivot_df[\"state_name\"].map(state_abbrev)\n",
        "pivot_df = pivot_df.dropna(subset=[\"state_code\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_ai_premium = px.choropleth(\n",
        "    pivot_df,\n",
        "    locations=\"state_code\",\n",
        "    locationmode=\"USA-states\",\n",
        "    color=\"premium_pct\",\n",
        "    scope=\"usa\",\n",
        "    hover_name=\"state_name\",\n",
        "    hover_data={\n",
        "        \"AI-related\": \":,.0f\",\n",
        "        \"Non-AI\": \":,.0f\",\n",
        "        \"premium_dollars\": \":,.0f\",\n",
        "        \"premium_pct\": \":.1f\",\n",
        "        \"state_code\": False\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    color_continuous_scale=\"RdYlGn\",\n",
        "    title=\"AI Salary Premium (%) by State\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_ai_premium.update_layout(\n",
        "    template=\"plotly_white\",\n",
        "    height=550\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "#fig_ai_premium.show()"
      ],
